titleStmt.title: An ordinance of the Commons assembled in Parliament, for a bill ordered to be sent to the Kings Maiesty, to be transmitted under the great Seale of England. Concerning the qualifications of the knights, citizens, and burgesses, who shall be admitted to sit in Parliament for this kingdome of Ireland. And for disbanding of those who refuse to take the oath. This ordinance of the House of Commons (in Parliament assembled) is printed and published according to order.
